  "prompt": "How do you build a kotatsu table?",
  "response": "Building a kotatsu table involves several steps:\n\nMaterials needed:\n1. Wooden table frame\n2. Blanket/futon\n3. Electric heating element\n4. Tabletop\n5. Basic woodworking tools\n\nSteps:\n1. Create the table frame\n- Build a low wooden table with sturdy legs\n- Typical height is around 12-16 inches\n- Ensure frame is stable and level\n\n2. Install heating element\n- Purchase a specialized kotatsu heater\n- Mount heater underneath the table surface\n- Connect to power supply safely\n- Ensure proper ventilation\n\n3. Add table surface\n- Create a removable tabletop\n- Position it above the heating element\n- Make sure it fits securely\n\n4. Prepare blanket/futon\n- Use a thick, heavy blanket that drapes over table edges\n- Place blanket between frame and tabletop\n- Blanket helps trap heat\n\n5. Final setup\n- Place heating element\n- Cover with blanket\n- Add tabletop\n- Ensure electrical connections are secure\n\nSafety tips:\n- Follow manufacturer's instructions\n- Use proper electrical connections\n- Don't leave heater unattended\n- Keep flammable materials away\n\nConsider professional assistance if you're not comfortable with woodworking or electrical work.",
